  <p class="">For press or media inquiries, please contact <a href="mailto:press@vrchat.com">press@vrchat.com</a></p><p class="">We‚Äôre hiring! <a href="https://hello.vrchat.com/careers">Check out  open positions on our site</a></p>]]></description><media:content type="image/png" url="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/1709308850287-91ILLTO0IP3VH27VWI9H/Social+Post++-+Start.png?format=1500w" medium="image" isDefault="true" width="1500" height="844"><media:title type="plain">Come on and Join the Space Jam!</media:title></media:content></item><item><title>Paid Subscriptions: Now in Open Beta!</title><dc:creator>Tupper</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 22 Nov 2023 23:59:00 +0000</pubDate><link>https://hello.vrchat.com/blog/paid-subscriptions-beta</link><guid isPermaLink="false">5f0770791aaf57311515b23d:61e9ceaed5e64e33580b3b7e:655d39ecc1e65b4b80b3f3f5</guid><description><![CDATA[<iframe scrolling="no" allowfullscreen src="//www.youtube.com/embed/mgcAvzNVmRo?wmode=opaque" width="854" frameborder="0" height="480"></iframe>




  <p class="">From awe-inspiring avatars to mesmerizing worlds, the ingenuity of our creators ‚Äî streamers, roleplayers, musicians, dancers, and more ‚Äî has always been the heartbeat of VRChat. But what if this creativity could fuel not just passion, but livelihoods too? </p><p class="">With Paid Subscriptions, that‚Äôs no longer a ‚Äúwhat-if.‚Äù</p><p class="">Over the last few years, we‚Äôve talked about introducing something we‚Äôve called the ‚ÄúCreator Economy,‚Äù and we‚Äôre finally ready to reveal what the first step of that effort is going to look like: Paid Subscriptions!</p><p class="">As it stands now, creators within VRChat have to jump through a series of complicated, frustrating hoops if they want to make money from their creations. For creators, this means having to set up a veritable Rube Goldberg machine, often requiring multiple external platforms and a lot of jank. For supporters, it means having to sign up for those same platforms‚Ä¶ and then hope that the creator you‚Äôre trying to support set everything up correctly.</p><p class="">The end result is a mess. So we‚Äôve built something better.</p><h3>Introducing Paid Subscriptions: The First Phase of VRChat‚Äôs Creator Economy</h3><p class="">Paid Subscriptions allow everyone in VRChat to directly support the creators they love with dramatically less friction. At the same time, Paid Subscriptions also empower creators to build far more interesting creations with their supporters in mind.</p><p class="">Creators can now easily create VIP rooms in their instances that only their subscribers can access. Or maybe they could have a special car or jet that is only available if you‚Äôre a supporter. Or maybe supporters get a special icon above their head in their instances. Or, for event runners, priority or exclusive access to your events!</p><h3>How Do Paid Subscriptions Work?</h3><p class="">All VRChat players can now purchase VRChat Credits with real-life money. </p><p class="">You can spend these on certain perks that creators set via Groups. Generally, you‚Äôll go to a creator‚Äôs Group page, click the ‚ÄúStore‚Äù button, and then be presented with a list of things you can purchase.</p><p class="">These individual perks are known as Paid Subscriptions! You can purchase one for a certain amount of time: say a month, three months, a year. These are currently not recurring ‚Äì but will be in the future!</p><p class="">Paid Subscriptions work directly with Udon, allowing creators an almost unlimited amount of freedom to build perks for their supporters.</p><h3>What‚Äôs the Revenue Split?</h3>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
