  <p class="">For press or media inquiries, please contact <a href="mailto:press@vrchat.com">press@vrchat.com</a></p><p class="">We‚Äôre hiring! <a href="https://hello.vrchat.com/careers">Check out  open positions on our site</a></p>]]></description><media:content type="image/png" url="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/1692223686348-TD6IFM58A7ADBHPE7QKX/DevUpdate_Android_ALPHA.png?format=1500w" medium="image" isDefault="true" width="1500" height="844"><media:title type="plain">VRChat Mobile Beta Now Live!</media:title></media:content></item><item><title>Community Guidelines Update</title><dc:creator>Tupper</dc:creator><pubDate>Wed, 02 Aug 2023 19:33:27 +0000</pubDate><link>https://hello.vrchat.com/blog/community-guidelines-update</link><guid isPermaLink="false">5f0770791aaf57311515b23d:61e9ceaed5e64e33580b3b7e:64caac8d009e736565175896</guid><description><![CDATA[<p class="">The VRChat community is what makes our platform so strong ‚Äì without you, VRChat would simply not exist. To be blunt, the community is the reason why we come into the (proverbial) office every day.</p><p class="">In order to keep that community safe, we‚Äôve always instructed our users to follow our <a href="https://hello.vrchat.com/community-guidelines">Community Guidelines</a> and our <a href="https://hello.vrchat.com/legal">Terms of Service</a>.</p><p class="">As VRChat has grown, however, we‚Äôve started to feel like our <a href="https://hello.vrchat.com/community-guidelines">Community Guidelines</a> have become a bit of a relic. We wanted to change them so that they were easier to understand, more relevant to our current community, and that they were directed at both users and creators.</p><p class="">So we‚Äôve done that! <strong>The </strong><a href="https://hello.vrchat.com/community-guidelines"><strong>Community Guidelines</strong></a><strong> have been completely updated.</strong> Instead of summarizing them here, we strongly suggest that you read through them. They‚Äôve been completely rewritten from the ground up, so it‚Äôd be hard to summarize them anyway!</p><p class="">Additionally, <strong>we‚Äôve created a new set of guidelines specifically for creators ‚Äì aptly titled the </strong><a href="https://hello.vrchat.com/creator-guidelines"><strong>Creator Guidelines</strong></a><strong>.</strong></p><p class=""><strong>Generally speaking, none of these guidelines are new or a surprise. </strong>These new guidelines do <em>not</em> come with a change to how we‚Äôre enforcing our rules, but it does mean that our guidelines are much more clear!</p><p class="">It‚Äôs strongly suggested that all creators read through these guidelines. While they likely won‚Äôt come as a surprise, we thought that breaking them out and codifying them would make our expectations of our creator community clearer.</p><p class="">You‚Äôll also notice that, at the top right of both pages, there is a date showing when they were last updated. While we won‚Äôt always announce changes with a blog post like this, whenever we do make a change, that date will change.</p><p class="">We will discuss these Guidelines in our <a href="https://ask.vrchat.com/c/official/dev-updates/32">Dev Update</a> thread for tomorrow (August 3 2023), so if you have questions or requests for clarifications, check out that thread when it goes up!</p>]]></description></item><item><title>Introducing the Creator Economy</title><dc:creator>Tupper</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 18 May 2023 19:30:25 +0000</pubDate><link>https://hello.vrchat.com/blog/creator-economy</link><guid isPermaLink="false">5f0770791aaf57311515b23d:61e9ceaed5e64e33580b3b7e:646674fb3f8d9841fc22668c</guid><description><![CDATA[<figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <img data-stretch="false" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/9f8357b9-7b56-46c4-8c80-f1bd39671e50/Title_Frame.png" data-image-dimensions="1920x1080" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" elementtiming="system-image-block" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/9f8357b9-7b56-46c4-8c80-f1bd39671e50/Title_Frame.png?format=1000w" width="1920" height="1080" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 767px) 100vw, 100vw" onload="this.classList.add(&quot;loaded&quot;)" srcset="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/9f8357b9-7b56-46c4-8c80-f1bd39671e50/Title_Frame.png?format=100w 100w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/9f8357b9-7b56-46c4-8c80-f1bd39671e50/Title_Frame.png?format=300w 300w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/9f8357b9-7b56-46c4-8c80-f1bd39671e50/Title_Frame.png?format=500w 500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/9f8357b9-7b56-46c4-8c80-f1bd39671e50/Title_Frame.png?format=750w 750w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/9f8357b9-7b56-46c4-8c80-f1bd39671e50/Title_Frame.png?format=1000w 1000w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/9f8357b9-7b56-46c4-8c80-f1bd39671e50/Title_Frame.png?format=1500w 1500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/9f8357b9-7b56-46c4-8c80-f1bd39671e50/Title_Frame.png?format=2500w 2500w" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-loader="sqs">

            
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="">VRChat has a lot of creators ‚Äì avatar and world makers, streamers, roleplayers, comedians, actors, musicians, dancers, and many, many more. There‚Äôs a good chance you might be a fan of a few of them! </p><p class="">Wouldn‚Äôt it be great if you could easily support them from within the VRChat client ‚Äì maybe even helping them turn their hobby into something that could help pay the bills?</p><p class="">We think so ‚Äì and that‚Äôs why we‚Äôve been working on VRChat‚Äôs Creator Economy for the last few years. We last mentioned we were working on the Creator Economy <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QBQnCxtDaso">way back in 2021</a>. Since then, we‚Äôve been busy working out exactly how we want it to work, and we‚Äôre now ready to start talking about it!</p>





















  
  








  <iframe scrolling="no" allowfullscreen src="//www.youtube.com/embed/e93QzjnVf9g?wmode=opaque" width="854" frameborder="0" height="480"></iframe>




  <p class="">Two big points first: while we‚Äôre going to start talking about it today, it‚Äôs unlikely that this system is going to be out soon. We expect it to launch sometime this year, but we aren‚Äôt ready to make any concrete promise on a release date. Second, we‚Äôll be opening up a beta ‚Äì but unlike most betas we run, this will be closed. More on that later!</p><p class="">So with that out of the way, let‚Äôs get into it.</p><h3>How Will the Creator Economy Work?</h3><p class="">It‚Äôs unlikely that one single solution will work for every type of creator in VRChat. So, we‚Äôre going to be introducing multiple ways to interact with the Creator Economy.</p><p class="">First, we‚Äôll be releasing a system where you can support creators through the Groups system. By supporting a creator‚Äôs Group, you can gain access to special roles that unlock certain features and perks you otherwise wouldn‚Äôt have.</p><p class="">World creators will be able to code in different features that dynamically change based on purchased group roles. So, for example, if you have a specific role, you might gain access to a  certain room or item that you might not otherwise have access to.</p><p class="">But as we said above, the intent here is to support more than just the traditional groups people think of as creators in VRChat. For example, do you usually host events in VRChat? Well, now you‚Äôll be able to host VIP events for your supporters. </p><p class="">All of this would be happening from within VRChat. If you‚Äôre a creator, that means that your supporters don‚Äôt have to jump through hoops or sign up for other websites. Likewise, if you‚Äôre someone that wants to support a creator in VRChat, you can do so just by clicking a few buttons in the client. </p><p class="">Our goal is to make this as easy as possible. If you have a great time at an event, or you‚Äôre playing around in a new world, we want you to be able to say thank you without having to jump through hoops.</p><h3>What About Avatar Creators?</h3><p class="">We‚Äôre very aware of how many avatar creators would love a system that makes it easier for users to find and buy their wares. Right now, it‚Äôs‚Ä¶complicated.</p><p class="">We‚Äôd like to streamline that process, and we have some good ideas for how to do so, but that‚Äôs something that will likely come after the initial release of the Creator Economy. We‚Äôll be pushing out the Group-centric systems first. </p><p class="">While we have a pretty good idea of how we‚Äôd like things to work internally, we‚Äôre going to keep the specifics under wraps for now. Once again, check the bi-weekly Dev Updates for ongoing development information! (You can find those <a href="https://ask.vrchat.com/c/official/31">here</a>!)</p><h3>Closed Beta</h3><p class="">Earlier, we‚Äôd mentioned that there‚Äôs going to be a Closed Beta for the Creator Economy. We wanted to talk a bit about that, as it‚Äôs going to look very different from other betas for us.</p><p class="">First, when we say Closed Beta, we really mean it ‚Äì we only intend on inviting in 10 - 20 creators at first. Up until now, we‚Äôve been testing these systems internally, but before releasing them to the public (even in a beta format) we want to make sure that they both actually work and that creators find them easy to use.</p><p class="">That first point can‚Äôt be stressed enough! We have to make sure that this system is solid at launch, as people will be putting their real, actual money into it. A bug could mean someone is losing money into the code void. And we obviously don‚Äôt want that!</p><p class="">Second, we don‚Äôt want to release something that might seem awesome to us, but that our top creators think is junk. As with all creator-based systems, we want to ensure that they actually interface well with their creative processes. We want to reduce friction for creators, after all, not create more of it!</p><p class="">All of this is to say that the beta is for‚Ä¶ well, <em>testing</em>. For anyone that isn‚Äôt invited to this particular beta: the only thing you‚Äôre missing out on is a lot of jargon, and probably a lot of really annoying bugs! This isn‚Äôt an ‚Äúearly access‚Äù program, but rather an earnest attempt to make sure we‚Äôre delivering the best possible economy we can to VRChat.</p><h3>Looking Forward</h3><p class="">We‚Äôve been working on the VRChat Creator Economy for a long time. We realize that the introduction of the Creator Economy ‚Äì much like Groups ‚Äì has the potential to dramatically change the VRChat community. It‚Äôs for that reason we‚Äôve been carefully debating every aspect of this system behind the scenes for years.</p><p class="">To be blunt, we want to make sure to get it right.</p><p class="">For that reason, the Creator Economy is going to be in beta for longer than most features. It‚Äôs likely that it won‚Äôt be until later this year that it‚Äôs released to everyone. With that said, though, we‚Äôll be updating the community on its progress as the year goes on in our bi-weekly Developer Updates. </p><p class="">Thanks for reading, and as always, thank you for loving VRChat as much as we do!</p>





















  
  



