  <p class="">Now the moment all of you have been waiting for‚Ä¶ presenting our 10 Winners, each receiving one year of VRChat Plus:</p><p class=""><em>In no particular order</em></p><p class=""><strong>Alex by Marino</strong></p><p class=""><strong>AMP by MR_em</strong></p><p class=""><strong>Axelottie by Nae the Loud</strong></p><p class=""><strong>Bean by FancySocks</strong></p><p class=""><strong>Bhird by meltingarmymen</strong></p><p class=""><strong>Funkmaster Jman by Raujinn</strong></p><p class=""><strong>Pupbot by Widget365</strong></p><p class=""><strong>Rune by -Darian-</strong></p><p class=""><strong>TV by Cozu</strong></p><p class=""><strong>Xperiment by speedbuiz</strong></p><p class="">While our jaws were constantly on the floor thanks to the amazing quality of the avatars all of our creators submitted, these ten really impressed us! We think they do an especially good job of showcasing the diversity VRChat has to offer. As we said before, it wasn‚Äôt easy selecting only ten winners. The sheer quality of incredible creators who submitted their work to this Jam was mind blowing.</p><p class="">Sometime in the next week, we‚Äôll be sending out emails with feedback to all participants who submitted an avatar. Please keep an eye out for that!</p><p class="">Didn‚Äôt make it to the finals this time? Don‚Äôt fret! After the incredible success of this Jam, you can be certain that another one will be coming in the future.</p><p class="">Thank you all once again for participating. We can‚Äôt wait to see what you create next!</p>





















  
  



<hr />&nbsp;


  <p class="">For press or media inquiries, please contact <a href="mailto:press@vrchat.com">press@vrchat.com</a></p><p class="">We‚Äôre hiring! <a href="https://hello.vrchat.com/careers">Check out  open positions on our site</a></p>]]></description><media:content type="image/png" url="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/1680840182795-MJ8Y3BK9503AATBOGB98/thumb2.png?format=1500w" medium="image" isDefault="true" width="1280" height="720"><media:title type="plain">Announcing the Avatars for Everyone Winners</media:title></media:content></item><item><title>April Developer Update</title><dc:creator>Tupper</dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 06 Apr 2023 23:58:43 +0000</pubDate><link>https://hello.vrchat.com/blog/april-dev-update</link><guid isPermaLink="false">5f0770791aaf57311515b23d:61e9ceaed5e64e33580b3b7e:642f0f1699b16e594c74ab82</guid><description><![CDATA[<iframe scrolling="no" allowfullscreen src="//www.youtube.com/embed/5K4mMn_JLpk?wmode=opaque" width="854" frameborder="0" height="480"></iframe>




  <p class="">This month, we wanted to share a few things we‚Äôve been working on behind the scenes: <strong>Groups Updates</strong>, <strong>Localization</strong>, and <strong>Impostors</strong>.&nbsp;</p><p class="">We‚Äôre cooking a lot up so this is hardly an exhaustive list, but we wanted to break down these three features and talk about them in this month‚Äôs Developer Update!</p><p class="">Let‚Äôs not waste any time, and jump right into it. Up first: Group Updates!</p><h3><strong>Group Updates</strong></h3><p class="">As we said back in November, the intention for Groups was to release the bones of the system, and then over the next few months build on that foundation, adding in new features as we see fit.</p><p class="">The plan was to add search immediately after launch. However, after exploring things a bit more, we decided to prioritize a few other features, including some specific features that were requested by the community.</p><p class="">One of the biggest requests for Groups at launch was more Group-specific instance types. Well, you‚Äôre getting them! We‚Äôll be adding in two new instance types: Groups Plus and Groups Public.</p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <img data-stretch="false" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/170398c9-7f3d-48fd-9880-69819ed440b8/groups1.png" data-image-dimensions="1906x1070" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" elementtiming="system-image-block" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/170398c9-7f3d-48fd-9880-69819ed440b8/groups1.png?format=1000w" width="1906" height="1070" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 767px) 100vw, 100vw" onload="this.classList.add(&quot;loaded&quot;)" srcset="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/170398c9-7f3d-48fd-9880-69819ed440b8/groups1.png?format=100w 100w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/170398c9-7f3d-48fd-9880-69819ed440b8/groups1.png?format=300w 300w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/170398c9-7f3d-48fd-9880-69819ed440b8/groups1.png?format=500w 500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/170398c9-7f3d-48fd-9880-69819ed440b8/groups1.png?format=750w 750w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/170398c9-7f3d-48fd-9880-69819ed440b8/groups1.png?format=1000w 1000w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/170398c9-7f3d-48fd-9880-69819ed440b8/groups1.png?format=1500w 1500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/170398c9-7f3d-48fd-9880-69819ed440b8/groups1.png?format=2500w 2500w" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-loader="sqs">

            
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class=""><strong>Groups Plus</strong> instances are identical to Friends Plus instances in a lot of ways. If you're a friend of someone who is in the Group Plus instance, you can join, even if you're not a group member! The major difference is that Group moderators will be able to control and moderate the instance.</p><p class="">This way, you can still enjoy many of the benefits of having a private Group instance, but with the added benefit of letting in people who aren‚Äôt part of that group. If you: run events, want a less exclusive-feeling environment, or just like to stay on green but want to know who you‚Äôre interacting with, this is for you.</p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <img data-stretch="false" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/b0f3b841-9c3a-405e-9012-9734d3cd3717/groups2.png" data-image-dimensions="1902x1068" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" elementtiming="system-image-block" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/b0f3b841-9c3a-405e-9012-9734d3cd3717/groups2.png?format=1000w" width="1902" height="1068" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 767px) 100vw, 100vw" onload="this.classList.add(&quot;loaded&quot;)" srcset="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/b0f3b841-9c3a-405e-9012-9734d3cd3717/groups2.png?format=100w 100w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/b0f3b841-9c3a-405e-9012-9734d3cd3717/groups2.png?format=300w 300w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/b0f3b841-9c3a-405e-9012-9734d3cd3717/groups2.png?format=500w 500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/b0f3b841-9c3a-405e-9012-9734d3cd3717/groups2.png?format=750w 750w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/b0f3b841-9c3a-405e-9012-9734d3cd3717/groups2.png?format=1000w 1000w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/b0f3b841-9c3a-405e-9012-9734d3cd3717/groups2.png?format=1500w 1500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/b0f3b841-9c3a-405e-9012-9734d3cd3717/groups2.png?format=2500w 2500w" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-loader="sqs">

            
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class=""><strong>Groups Public</strong> are ‚Äì you guessed it! ‚Äì like public instances. Except Group moderators can control and moderate them. This way, Groups can host their own moderated and/or special interest public instances <em>and</em> they‚Äôll be visible alongside other public instances!</p><p class="">Now you can host a public event and keep things‚Ä¶ well, a little less chaotic.</p><p class="">The next major feature we‚Äôll be adding to Groups is <strong>Queues</strong>.</p><p class="">Ever wanted to join an instance but it was full? What if you could get in line instead? Now, if you attempt to join a full instance, you can join a queue instead of getting the dreaded ‚Äúinstance is full‚Äù error message!</p><p class="">When space is available, VRChat will notify you and hold your spot‚Äîcurrently for 2 minutes‚Äîso you can join. No more getting sent home or spamming "world join" to try and reach your friends.</p><p class="">Of course, these aren‚Äôt the only features that are coming for Groups. We intend to continue iterating and adding features to Groups throughout the year.</p><p class="sqsrte-small"><strong>World Capacity Changes</strong></p><p class="">Along with the Queue system, we‚Äôre making some changes to the ‚Äúsoft cap‚Äù and ‚Äúhard cap‚Äù system!</p><p class="">Right now the capacity of a VRChat world is determined by a value called the ‚Äúcapacity.‚Äù This is a value that you set in the SDK, or on the website when viewing your own world.</p><p class="">This value is then used as the ‚Äúsoft cap‚Äù, or the amount of people you see in the UI that are allowed in a world‚Äîlike 12 out of 16. When you‚Äôre at or above the soft cap, the UI and a few other things change behavior accordingly.</p><p class="">The ‚Äúhard cap‚Äù is the maximum number of people permitted in instances of that world. Currently, it's two times the capacity that you set. That means if your capacity is set to 10, then your soft cap is also 10, and the hard cap is 20. But the overall hard cap is 80, set by us.</p><p class="">But that‚Äôs not it! There are a few exceptions: the world author and instance creator can always join that instance, even if it‚Äôs at hard cap! So, the absolute maximum is 82... or it would be, if there weren‚Äôt other exceptions for things like VRChat system-level accounts.</p><p class="">This is horribly confusing. So we‚Äôre changing it.</p><p class="">You‚Äôll now be able to define two explicit values: the ‚Äúrecommended‚Äù capacity, and the ‚Äúmaximum‚Äù capacity. You can set these to be the same or different!</p><p class="">The recommended capacity is the maximum number of users you‚Äôd expect to be in the world for an ideal experience. Treat this the same way as the previous soft cap value; the UI and application will react in similar ways when you‚Äôre past the recommended capacity.</p><p class="">The ‚Äúmaximum capacity‚Äù can now be set by you, and it no longer has to be precisely double the recommended capacity! It just has to be greater than or equal to <em>your</em> recommended capacity, and less than or equal to <em>our</em> maximum capacity of 80.&nbsp;</p><p class="">If you want to set your recommended capacity to 20, and maximum to 25, you can do that! Or 20/80, 20/20, or even 1/1 for a solo experience.</p><p class="">The UI will now show the maximum capacity instead of the recommended capacity when viewing an instance. We‚Äôll still display the recommended capacity alongside in some form.</p><p class="">You can also choose to set your maximum capacity to 80, or the ‚Äúglobal maximum‚Äù. If we ever increase the global maximum capacity past this, your world will automatically bump up to that number. But, this isn‚Äôt something we‚Äôre thinking about doing anytime soon.</p><p class="">As said before, world authors, instance creators, and other exceptions may drive your actual possible occupants past 80, so make sure you account for that in your Udon scripts.</p><p class="">You‚Äôll also notice some nuanced changes to how we handle full instances:</p><ul data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="">&nbsp;You'll no longer be able to invite someone to a full instance.</p></li><li><p class="">If someone requests an invite from you while you‚Äôre in a full instance, you'll be told you cannot send the invite, and can reply with ‚ÄúThe instance is full, sorry!‚Äù</p></li><li><p class="">No more sitting in a loading screen for a minute only to get hit with a ‚ÄúHONK, sorry, instance is full‚Äù message.</p></li></ul><p class="">We‚Äôll have some more information available soon about these changes. Keep an eye on the text Dev Updates in our Ask forums.</p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
