        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <img data-stretch="false" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/370f1cbe-eaa3-4c8a-846e-2fd0b1ba0bcf/languages.png" data-image-dimensions="1892x1064" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" elementtiming="system-image-block" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/370f1cbe-eaa3-4c8a-846e-2fd0b1ba0bcf/languages.png?format=1000w" width="1892" height="1064" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 767px) 100vw, 100vw" onload="this.classList.add(&quot;loaded&quot;)" srcset="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/370f1cbe-eaa3-4c8a-846e-2fd0b1ba0bcf/languages.png?format=100w 100w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/370f1cbe-eaa3-4c8a-846e-2fd0b1ba0bcf/languages.png?format=300w 300w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/370f1cbe-eaa3-4c8a-846e-2fd0b1ba0bcf/languages.png?format=500w 500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/370f1cbe-eaa3-4c8a-846e-2fd0b1ba0bcf/languages.png?format=750w 750w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/370f1cbe-eaa3-4c8a-846e-2fd0b1ba0bcf/languages.png?format=1000w 1000w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/370f1cbe-eaa3-4c8a-846e-2fd0b1ba0bcf/languages.png?format=1500w 1500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/370f1cbe-eaa3-4c8a-846e-2fd0b1ba0bcf/languages.png?format=2500w 2500w" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-loader="sqs">

            
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <h3><strong>Localization</strong></h3><p class="">VRChat is enjoyed by people all over the world. It‚Äôd be fair to say that we have a pretty linguistically diverse community! Spend some time in a few random instances and you‚Äôll probably hear a few different languages, despite VRChat‚Äôs English-only UI.</p><p class="">We‚Äôre changing that.</p><p class="">We‚Äôve already translated the Quick Menu and Main Menu tooltips, and will eventually move on to the rest of the client, starting with German, French, Italian, Japanese, Korean, and Spanish. Eventually, we‚Äôll add other languages.</p><p class="">But our current translations are a bit literal and awkward. Long-time VRChat users likely have a better idea of what things are called. Or, they might have developed colloquial names for things that are commonly used in their language that we just don‚Äôt know about.</p><p class="">So, using a platform called Crowdin, community members can submit localization suggestions that will be reviewed by proofreaders and some bilingual VRChat developers. Once approved, the changes will be queued up and ready to go for the next client release.</p><p class="">And Crowdin is pretty easy to use! For those interested, <a href="https://docs.vrchat.com/docs/suggesting-localization-changes">check out our docs here</a>.</p><p class="">Of course, we want to think of a way to properly thank the localization volunteers who are submitting suggestions‚Ä¶but we aren‚Äôt quite sure what that looks like yet. Or a timeframe. So please keep an eye out for something concrete!</p><h3><strong>Impostors</strong></h3><p class="">Finally, let‚Äôs talk about something we‚Äôve been diligently working on for the past year: Impostors.</p><p class="">Impostors are essentially like avatar body doubles, allowing people to see your avatar in situations when they‚Äôd usually see a fallback avatar or robot. That means that even if you‚Äôve never uploaded a cross-platform version of your avatar, or if someone has your performance level blocked, they‚Äôll still be able to see an ‚Äúimpostor‚Äù of your avatar!</p><p class="">They‚Äôre created with the push of a button, and will one day be auto-generated. Impostors aren‚Äôt a mirror image of your avatar, but they‚Äôre pretty close!</p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <img data-stretch="false" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/20e99b69-6af8-4202-ba40-accbccc09261/imposters2.png" data-image-dimensions="1894x1074" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" elementtiming="system-image-block" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/20e99b69-6af8-4202-ba40-accbccc09261/imposters2.png?format=1000w" width="1894" height="1074" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 767px) 100vw, 100vw" onload="this.classList.add(&quot;loaded&quot;)" srcset="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/20e99b69-6af8-4202-ba40-accbccc09261/imposters2.png?format=100w 100w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/20e99b69-6af8-4202-ba40-accbccc09261/imposters2.png?format=300w 300w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/20e99b69-6af8-4202-ba40-accbccc09261/imposters2.png?format=500w 500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/20e99b69-6af8-4202-ba40-accbccc09261/imposters2.png?format=750w 750w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/20e99b69-6af8-4202-ba40-accbccc09261/imposters2.png?format=1000w 1000w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/20e99b69-6af8-4202-ba40-accbccc09261/imposters2.png?format=1500w 1500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/20e99b69-6af8-4202-ba40-accbccc09261/imposters2.png?format=2500w 2500w" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-loader="sqs">

            
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="">Until now, we‚Äôve used the fallback system: You‚Äôd select a more performant, cross-platform avatar that would appear when yours otherwise couldn‚Äôt be displayed. In many cases, this fallback avatar wouldn‚Äôt look anything like your avatar and you didn‚Äôt have a coherent identity.</p><p class="">That was confusing and frustrating for both you and the people you‚Äôd hang out with.</p><p class="">Even if you have the technical knowledge to build a custom fallback or cross-platform avatar, you might just not have the time. You couldn‚Äôt be seen how you‚Äôd want to be seen.</p><p class="">Wouldn‚Äôt it be nice, in those specific cases, if you could just press a button and generate a cross-platform avatar based on whatever avatar you chose? We think so.</p><p class="">We‚Äôve been testing this tech internally for some time now, and are pretty confident that it can handle most avatars. Of course, there will be some exceptions. This is cutting-edge stuff, after all!</p>





















  
  














































  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            
                
                
                
                
                
                
                
                <img data-stretch="false" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/cfb7ef9a-597b-41d0-a46e-db4f91621d01/imposters.png" data-image-dimensions="1894x1074" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" elementtiming="system-image-block" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/cfb7ef9a-597b-41d0-a46e-db4f91621d01/imposters.png?format=1000w" width="1894" height="1074" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, (max-width: 767px) 100vw, 100vw" onload="this.classList.add(&quot;loaded&quot;)" srcset="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/cfb7ef9a-597b-41d0-a46e-db4f91621d01/imposters.png?format=100w 100w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/cfb7ef9a-597b-41d0-a46e-db4f91621d01/imposters.png?format=300w 300w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/cfb7ef9a-597b-41d0-a46e-db4f91621d01/imposters.png?format=500w 500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/cfb7ef9a-597b-41d0-a46e-db4f91621d01/imposters.png?format=750w 750w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/cfb7ef9a-597b-41d0-a46e-db4f91621d01/imposters.png?format=1000w 1000w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/cfb7ef9a-597b-41d0-a46e-db4f91621d01/imposters.png?format=1500w 1500w, https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f0770791aaf57311515b23d/cfb7ef9a-597b-41d0-a46e-db4f91621d01/imposters.png?format=2500w 2500w" loading="lazy" decoding="async" data-loader="sqs">

            
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





  <p class="">Sometime in the next few months, we will be introducing Impostors into VRChat. This feature is being rolled out in stages.</p><p class="">Once this feature is live, you'll be able to generate an Impostor for your avatar via the VRChat website. As a note, you'll only be able to generate Impostors for avatars that you own and have uploaded.</p><p class="">Impostor generation should be pretty fast! Once your Impostor has finished generating, you‚Äôll receive an email letting you know that it‚Äôs ready or if the process failed.</p><p class="">Other users will only see your Impostor if there is no other version of your avatar available for the platform they are on.</p><p class="">Prefer using a fallback avatar instead? There‚Äôs a toggle to turn them on or off. And, if you want to see what your impostor looks like, you can toggle between your avatar‚Äôs actual model and its Impostor.</p><p class="">Keep in mind that this is a soft launch. We‚Äôre pretty happy with how Impostors look and feel but it‚Äôs not a finished product just yet. We anticipate that some Impostors might look weird, might totally break, or might not even generate at all. We‚Äôre going to be perfecting this system as time goes on until we‚Äôre completely happy with it.</p><h3><strong>Wrapping Things Up</strong></h3><p class="">So‚Ä¶ we‚Äôve been working on a lot of new features. And this is only the tip of the iceberg. In the coming months, we‚Äôre going to have a lot of really exciting things to share.</p><p class="">Curious about what we‚Äôre working on? Keep an eye out for future Developer Updates, and follow our weekly Dev Updates every Thursday <a href="https://ask.vrchat.com/c/official/31">on our Ask forums</a> to stay in the loop.</p><p class="">As always, thank you for loving VRChat as much as we do. See you next time!</p>





















  
  



